data.text:
Marvin Williams - Points

Marvin Williams scores a career high 33 points (2008)

On January 25, 2008, Marvin Williams set his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 33 points in Atlanta's road win against Seattle, 90-99. He also had 7 rebounds, 2 assists, 3 steals and 1 block. He shot 12/20 from two, shooting at 60.0% from the field. He also shot 9/12 from the free-throw line.

Marvin Williams - Rebounds

Marvin Williams grabs a career high 18 rebounds (2017)

On March 10, 2017, Marvin Williams tied his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 18 rebounds in Charlotte's home win against Orlando, 121-81. He also had 12 points, 7 assists, 1 steal.

Marvin Williams - Assists

Marvin Williams gives a career high 7 assists (2007)

On January 12, 2007, Marvin Williams tied his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 7 assists in Atlanta's home win against Detroit, 99-93. He also had 12 points, 9 rebounds.

Marvin Williams - Steals

Marvin Williams has a career high 4 steals (2007)

On November 16, 2007, Marvin Williams tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 4 steals in Atlanta's home loss against Seattle, 123-126. He also had 18 points, 7 rebounds and 4 assists.

Marvin Williams - Blocks

Marvin Williams blocks a career high 4 shots (2008)

On January 13, 2008, Marvin Williams tied his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 4 blocks in Atlanta's home win against Chicago, 105-84. He also had 11 points, 4 rebounds and 3 assists.

Marvin Williams - Efficiency

Marvin Williams records a career high 37 efficiency rating (2012)

On April 22, 2012, Marvin Williams tied his career high in efficiency in a NBA game. That day he accomplished 37 efficiency in Atlanta's home loss against New York, 112-113. He also had 29 points, 11 rebounds.
